.TH HIVEMIND 1 "January 2026" "HiveMind 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hivemind, hm \- Intelligent multi-agent deployment system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hivemind
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.br
.B hm
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
HiveMind AutoDeploy is a multi-agent AI system that automatically deploys applications from source code repositories to AWS infrastructure.
.PP
The system uses 6 specialized agents:
.IP \(bu 2
HiveMind SA (Solutions Architect) - Analyzes documentation
.IP \(bu 2
HiveMind DevOps - Builds applications
.IP \(bu 2
HiveMind SysEng - Provisions AWS infrastructure
.IP \(bu 2
HiveMind Release-Engineer - Deploys applications
.IP \(bu 2
HiveMind SecOps - Hardens security
.IP \(bu 2
HiveMind Control Plane - Orchestrates all agents
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B deploy \fIREPO_URL\fR \fIDESCRIPTION\fR
Deploy an application from a repository
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-what-if
Simulate deployment without making changes (shows costs and resources)
.TP
.B \-\-verbose, -v
Show detailed output with all agent interactions
.RE
.TP
.B analyze \fIREPO_URL\fR
Analyze repository documentation without deploying (SA agent only)
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-output \fIFILE\fR
Save analysis to JSON file
.RE
.TP
.B status \fIDEPLOYMENT_ID\fR
Check deployment status and view logs
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-show-plan
Show deployment plan (for what-if deployments)
.TP
.B \-\-verbose, -v
Show detailed logs from all agents
.RE
.TP
.B plan \fIDEPLOYMENT_ID\fR
Show deployment plan created by SA agent
.TP
.B list
List all deployments
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-status \fISTATUS\fR
Filter by status (completed, failed, pending, etc.)
.TP
.B \-\-limit \fIN\fR
Limit number of results
.TP
.B \-\-verbose, -v
Show deployment statistics
.RE
.TP
.B retry \fIDEPLOYMENT_ID\fR
Retry a failed deployment from the last successful stage
.TP
.B rollback \fIDEPLOYMENT_ID\fR
Rollback deployment and delete all AWS resources
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-yes, -y
Skip confirmation prompt
.TP
.B \-\-verbose, -v
Show detailed rollback progress
.RE
.TP
.B destroy \fIDEPLOYMENT_ID\fR
Destroy deployment resources (alias for rollback)
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-force, -f
Skip confirmation prompt
.TP
.B \-\-skip-snapshot
Skip RDS final snapshot (faster but no backup)
.TP
.B \-\-verbose, -v
Show detailed destruction progress
.RE
.TP
.B reconcile \fIDEPLOYMENT_ID\fR
Reconcile deployment state with actual AWS resources
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-verbose, -v
Show detailed reconciliation results
.RE
.TP
.B find-orphans
Find orphaned HiveMind resources in AWS (resources without valid deployment)
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-verbose, -v
Show detailed resource information
.RE
.TP
.B cleanup
Clean up temporary and working files
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-backup
Create zip backup archive before cleaning
.TP
.B \-\-yes, -y
Skip confirmation prompt
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-state-dir \fIDIR\fR
Directory for deployment state files (default: ./HiveMind-Work/deployments)
.TP
.B \-\-region \fIREGION\fR
AWS region for infrastructure (default: us-east-1)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Simulate deployment (safe, no AWS charges):
.B hivemind deploy https://github.com/user/app "Test" --what-if
.TP
Real deployment:
.B hivemind deploy https://github.com/user/app "Production v1.0"
.TP
Check status with detailed logs:
.B hivemind status abc123def --verbose
.TP
Rollback deployment:
.B hivemind rollback abc123def
.TP
Clean up working files with backup:
.B hivemind cleanup --backup
.TP
List all completed deployments:
.B hivemind list --status completed
.TP
Find orphaned AWS resources:
.B hivemind find-orphans
.TP
Use short alias:
.B hm deploy https://github.com/user/app "Test" --what-if
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.hivemind/
Working files directory (deployments, analyzed repos, temp files)
.TP
.I ~/.hivemind/deployments/
Deployment state files (JSON)
.TP
.I ~/.hivemind/analyzed_repos/
Cloned repositories for analysis
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
AWS access key for authentication
.TP
.B AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
AWS secret key for authentication
.TP
.B AWS_REGION
Default AWS region (overridden by --region)
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Failure (deployment failed, invalid arguments, etc.)
.SH NOTES
.PP
HiveMind requires AWS credentials to deploy applications. Configure with:
.PP
.B aws configure
.PP
or set environment variables AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID and AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY.
.PP
What-if mode (--what-if) is safe and does not create any AWS resources or incur charges.
